text: Ukraine competed at the 2019 World Championships in Athletics, which was held in Doha between 27 September and 6 October, in a team of 41 athletes (17 men and 24 women), who participated in 22 (out of 49) events. Four athletes had been included to the final entry lists but did not participate in the events including Anastasiia Bryzgina, Yana Kachur, Ivanna Avramchuk (all were entered for women's and mixed 4×400 relays) and Dmytro Bikulov (mixed 4×400 relay). == Medalists == {|class=wikitable style="font-size:90%" !
